WEBVTT

00:01.410 --> 00:03.419
[epic music playing]

00:05.673 --> 00:08.065
[¶¶]

00:08.083 --> 00:09.425
[phone ringing]

00:11.328 --> 00:13.137
[phone ringing]

00:15.516 --> 00:18.166
Natalie Rogers,
events planning.

00:18.185 --> 00:19.852
Yes, Mrs. Miller.

00:19.928 --> 00:21.762
I confirmed the
venue this morning.

00:21.914 --> 00:23.355
You're all set for
your Christmas party.

00:25.934 --> 00:28.527
Natalie Rogers,
travel consultant.

00:28.604 --> 00:31.363
Hey, Mr. Walker,
how were your flights?

00:31.515 --> 00:32.589
I'm so glad.

00:32.608 --> 00:33.607
Yeah, you know,

00:33.759 --> 00:34.867
you can always string some
lights

00:35.018 --> 00:36.452
around a palm tree and
call it Christmas.

00:37.613 --> 00:40.522
Natalie Rogers,
custom gift-wrapping.

00:40.541 --> 00:43.042
Yes, I will be dropping those
off in about

00:43.193 --> 00:45.936
15 minutes.

00:45.954 --> 00:47.695
Mr. Ortiz!

00:47.715 --> 00:49.956
I finished the wreath
for your food truck.

00:50.109 --> 00:51.108
Even if the weather is
frightful,

00:51.126 --> 00:53.052
the chilies will keep you warm.

00:53.203 --> 00:54.294
Look.

00:54.446 --> 00:56.204
Muchas gracias.

00:56.223 --> 00:57.130
Wendy!

00:57.283 --> 00:58.540
Oh!

00:58.559 --> 01:01.060
Christmas cards,
addressed

01:01.136 --> 01:02.636
and stamped.

01:02.788 --> 01:04.121
Oh, I--

01:04.139 --> 01:05.956
Pop them in the mail and the let
the mailman do the rest.

01:05.974 --> 01:07.900
Thank you so much,
they're beautiful.

01:08.051 --> 01:10.402
Oh, I love hand-addressed cards,

01:10.554 --> 01:11.886
but with my penmanship

01:11.906 --> 01:14.222
no one would get them until
July.

01:14.241 --> 01:15.407
Well, I threw
in a couple of extra

01:15.484 --> 01:17.150
for Joshy and Becca

01:17.303 --> 01:18.744
direct from the North Pole.

01:18.895 --> 01:19.411
They'll be thrilled.

01:19.488 --> 01:20.562
Thank you so much.

01:20.581 --> 01:21.805
You're welcome.

01:21.824 --> 01:23.064
-Merry Christmas.
-Merry Christmas, Wendy.

01:23.142 --> 01:24.658
Yeah, took a little
creativity but you know

01:24.810 --> 01:27.419
I love a challenge.
Merry Christmas.

01:27.571 --> 01:30.422
Natalie, Sparky would be
so glad

01:30.499 --> 01:31.423
to see you.

01:31.500 --> 01:32.758
Come here.

01:32.909 --> 01:35.577
Sparky, your favorite
sitter is here.

01:35.596 --> 01:37.262
Hello, handsome.

01:37.414 --> 01:38.931
And these clothes.

01:39.007 --> 01:41.600
Who doesn't love to get all
dressed up for the holidays?

01:41.751 --> 01:46.012
We want to take him on a
Christmas cruise,

01:46.165 --> 01:49.608
but he gets terrible
sea-sickness.

01:49.685 --> 01:51.777
Well,
I am happy to.

01:51.854 --> 01:53.837
We are gonna have
a great time!

01:53.856 --> 01:56.340
We're gonna watch
It's a Wonderful Woof,

01:56.358 --> 01:58.450
and lap up eggnog, and sing
Christmas carols.

01:58.602 --> 02:00.010
[dog barks]

02:00.012 --> 02:02.287
See, he already knows
the opening to Jingle Bells.

02:02.439 --> 02:05.082
You're the best pet-sitter
anywhere we've ever had.

02:06.034 --> 02:07.459
[Natalie]
Thank you.

02:07.611 --> 02:09.019
[Girl's mom]
Natalie, thank you so much
for doing this.

02:09.037 --> 02:10.370
Of course.

02:10.522 --> 02:12.131
Are you sure I can't convince
you to come work for me?

02:12.207 --> 02:14.299
Thank you, but
I already have a job.

02:14.376 --> 02:15.801
You have eight jobs.

02:15.878 --> 02:17.194
That was just the
last time I counted.

02:17.212 --> 02:19.863
May have added
one or two since then.

02:19.882 --> 02:22.366
But why can't I since
I'm the Jacklyn of all trades.

02:22.384 --> 02:24.459
When are you gonna settle down
on one career?

02:24.478 --> 02:26.311
I don't know,
but I figure

02:26.388 --> 02:28.388
when I find the perfect thing,
I'll know it.

02:28.540 --> 02:30.131
And until then
I'm happy as I am.

02:30.151 --> 02:31.316
Well, I hope
you're not still waiting

02:31.468 --> 02:33.485
on the perfect thing
to do for Christmas.

02:33.562 --> 02:34.653
Thank you, but
I'm gonna spend Christmas

02:34.804 --> 02:36.488
with my cousin Olivia.

02:36.640 --> 02:37.990
I should probably
get going.

02:38.141 --> 02:40.325
Miles to go before I sleep
or at least a few more blocks.

02:40.402 --> 02:41.568
[chuckles]

02:41.720 --> 02:43.720
Be a good doggie, okay.

02:43.722 --> 02:44.830
Merry Christmas.

02:44.981 --> 02:46.481
Merry Christmas.

02:46.500 --> 02:48.225
Let's go, Sparky.

02:48.243 --> 02:49.168
Bye, Sparky.

02:49.244 --> 02:50.727
Bye.

02:50.746 --> 02:53.672
[phone ringing]

02:53.823 --> 02:55.674
Natalie Rogers,
custom wreaths or um,

02:55.751 --> 02:57.083
travel consultant.

02:57.236 --> 02:58.084
[Olivia]
Hi, it's Olivia.

02:58.237 --> 02:59.736
Olivia.

02:59.755 --> 03:01.180
I was just
talking about you.

03:01.331 --> 03:03.498
Are you back
from Rome yet?

03:03.517 --> 03:06.576
[Olivia]
No, I am not back from Rome.

03:06.595 --> 03:08.245
Uh, I guess you haven't
been following the news,

03:08.263 --> 03:09.504
have you?

03:09.523 --> 03:11.857
It's the big chill,
the new Ice Age.

03:13.101 --> 03:14.026
What are you talking about?

03:14.102 --> 03:15.343
I'm stranded here.

03:15.362 --> 03:16.862
Oh no.

03:17.013 --> 03:19.606
Yeah, looks like I won't be home
for Christmas, I'm so sorry.

03:19.758 --> 03:22.534
It's okay, it's um
I'll miss you,

03:22.611 --> 03:24.203
but don't worry about me,
lots of friends have offered to

03:24.354 --> 03:26.596
spend their Christmases
with me.

03:26.615 --> 03:27.597
[sighs]

03:27.616 --> 03:29.266
But are you okay?

03:29.268 --> 03:31.785
Yeah, but I wanted to kinda keep
this as a surprise,

03:33.214 --> 03:35.772
you know how I've been wanting
to open my restaurant for years.

03:35.774 --> 03:38.124
Well, I finally convinced
Chef Grimaldi to come over

03:38.277 --> 03:41.111
to Pine Valley
and be my partner.

03:41.129 --> 03:42.870
I remember him
from when you took me to

03:42.890 --> 03:44.389
Italy when I was little girl.

03:44.541 --> 03:46.225
I always thought he looked
just like Santa Claus.

03:46.301 --> 03:48.710
Oh, uh, so

03:48.729 --> 03:50.729
my plan was to open
on Christmas Eve

03:50.806 --> 03:53.232
with a big traditional
feast of Natale.

03:53.308 --> 03:54.808
You know how it is
in small towns, nothing is

03:54.960 --> 03:56.643
ever open on Christmas
and there's always

03:56.795 --> 03:58.962
a few people with no
place to go.

03:58.981 --> 04:00.964
No one should
be alone on Christmas.

04:00.983 --> 04:03.133
[Olivia]
Yeah, I feel terrible.

04:03.151 --> 04:04.892
We already had a handful
of reservations I'm gonna

04:04.912 --> 04:06.912
have to cancel, there's no
way Chef Grimaldi

04:07.063 --> 04:08.638
can do it on his own.

04:08.657 --> 04:11.141
Oh, I'm so sorry.

04:11.143 --> 04:12.918
Yeah, me too.

04:12.995 --> 04:15.754
Well, I wanted to let you
know, Merry Christmas.

04:15.905 --> 04:17.214
Merry Christmas, Olivia.

04:19.927 --> 04:21.167
[sighs]

04:21.320 --> 04:23.428
Problems are just opportunities
in work clothes.

04:30.271 --> 04:32.271
Hi, Mrs. Myers.

04:32.422 --> 04:35.256
This is Natalie Rogers,
Olivia's cousin.

04:35.276 --> 04:36.942
I have an idea.

04:37.093 --> 04:38.610
What do you know about
this restaurant

04:38.762 --> 04:40.112
she's planning on opening?

05:21.322 --> 05:23.280
[sighs]

05:25.400 --> 05:27.141
Come here.

05:27.161 --> 05:28.327
Come on.

05:31.073 --> 05:32.914
Alright.

05:52.578 --> 05:53.852
[sighs]

05:55.171 --> 05:57.356
Olivia always was
an optimist.

06:14.116 --> 06:15.957
Chef Rivaldi?

06:19.863 --> 06:21.213
You stay here.

06:21.364 --> 06:22.789
All dogs might go to
heaven but they should

06:22.941 --> 06:25.133
probably stay out of
restaurant kitchens.

07:03.090 --> 07:03.922
Stop right there,
you

07:04.073 --> 07:05.924
Ow!

07:06.001 --> 07:08.844
[speaking Italian]

07:11.673 --> 07:13.657
No, don't, let me go!

07:13.675 --> 07:15.434
[speaking Italian]

07:16.937 --> 07:19.396
Oh, that's so much better.

07:20.590 --> 07:21.898
Are you hurt?

07:27.839 --> 07:28.780
What?

07:28.932 --> 07:30.507
Are you hurt?

07:30.525 --> 07:31.524
No, no.

07:31.677 --> 07:32.784
No.

07:32.861 --> 07:34.268
II think it's fine.

07:34.288 --> 07:36.513
Now get outta
my kitchen, presto.

07:36.531 --> 07:38.865
Your kitchen, this is my cousin
Olivia's kitchen.

07:39.017 --> 07:41.460
So Olivia has a cousin?

07:41.536 --> 07:44.187
And the restaurant may
be hers, but the kitchen

07:44.189 --> 07:45.872
always belongs
to the chef.

07:46.024 --> 07:48.800
You can't be Chef Grimaldi.

07:48.952 --> 07:51.044
You're nothing
like Santa Claus.

07:51.196 --> 07:52.712
[laughs]

07:52.864 --> 07:54.306
Oh, you're thinking
of my uncle,

07:54.457 --> 07:56.308
Zio Lorenzo Grimaldi.

07:56.384 --> 07:59.202
Maybe I just look like my
[speaks Italian].

07:59.221 --> 08:00.704
But he was too old to
come to America,

08:00.722 --> 08:02.981
so I came instead.

08:03.058 --> 08:05.817
Sorry, I'm his nephew
Stefano Grimaldi.

08:05.969 --> 08:07.152
Ow.

08:07.229 --> 08:08.878
Uh, sorry.

08:08.897 --> 08:10.655
Uh, I don't know
the name of you.

08:10.732 --> 08:11.715
I'm Natalie.

08:11.733 --> 08:12.716
Rogers.

08:12.718 --> 08:14.326
Olivia's cousin.

08:14.477 --> 08:16.720
Oh, I should've known.

08:16.738 --> 08:18.571
See Olivia told me her
cousin was

08:18.724 --> 08:20.332
[inhales]

08:20.483 --> 08:21.500
la bella signorina.

08:21.576 --> 08:23.168
[chuckles]

08:23.245 --> 08:26.229
Oh, that's very nice of her.

08:26.248 --> 08:27.839
[sniffles]

08:27.916 --> 08:31.009
Oh, and it's very true.

08:31.086 --> 08:33.903
But what were you doing uh,
sneaking around my kitchen?

08:33.922 --> 08:35.329
I wasn't sneaking.

08:35.349 --> 08:37.015
Then that's not the word
for it,

08:37.166 --> 08:39.242
the sneaking and creeping.

08:39.261 --> 08:40.927
No, I wasn't doing any of those
thing,

08:41.079 --> 08:42.095
I was just looking
for the chef.

08:42.247 --> 08:44.689
[Mrs. Myers]
Yoohoo!

08:44.841 --> 08:46.191
Is anybody here?

08:48.177 --> 08:50.028
Mrs. Myers.

08:50.105 --> 08:51.196
Thanks for coming.

08:51.273 --> 08:52.589
Have you met my
cousin's best friend?

08:52.607 --> 08:54.015
-Hi.
-This is Mrs. Anna Myers.

08:54.034 --> 08:56.034
Stefano!

08:56.185 --> 08:58.870
[speaks in Italian]

08:59.022 --> 09:01.873
Oh, I see you have.

09:02.025 --> 09:04.601
And another one.

09:04.619 --> 09:07.379
What third time's
not a charm?

09:07.530 --> 09:09.548
Stefano's quite charming
enough.

09:09.699 --> 09:10.882
And who is this?

09:10.959 --> 09:12.384
[Natalie]
Sparky.

09:12.535 --> 09:14.386
I'm pet-sitting
for the holidays.

09:14.537 --> 09:16.221
Well, it was nice
to see you, huh.

09:16.372 --> 09:17.781
And to meet you, Sparky.

09:17.799 --> 09:19.724
But I must go otherwise my
sauce, huh, it will burn

09:19.801 --> 09:20.967
if I don't get back.

09:21.119 --> 09:22.710
-Oh, I just need to talk to you.
-No!

09:22.729 --> 09:24.971
A chef will never
let his food burn.

09:25.123 --> 09:26.898
Not for anything.

09:26.975 --> 09:28.024
Mamma mia.

09:30.462 --> 09:31.628
[Natalie]
Well, fine then.

09:31.646 --> 09:33.405
I brought your cousin's spare
keys, I'm sure

09:33.481 --> 09:34.906
she won't mind if you
stay in her house while

09:34.983 --> 09:35.965
you're here in town.

09:35.984 --> 09:37.224
Thank you.

09:37.244 --> 09:38.893
I really wanna go through
with the grand opening

09:38.912 --> 09:41.079
just as planned.

09:41.156 --> 09:42.305
[sighs]

09:42.324 --> 09:44.641
Well, there's a lot of
work to be done.

09:44.659 --> 09:46.918
Every problem is an opportunity
in disguise.

09:47.070 --> 09:48.645
If you insist.

09:48.663 --> 09:49.979
Well, let's get you settled in
and I'll tell you

09:49.998 --> 09:52.148
what I know of her plans.

09:52.167 --> 09:53.741
Unless I was
interrupting something.

09:53.760 --> 09:54.667
What?

09:54.820 --> 09:55.927
No.

09:56.004 --> 09:58.597
He's a very handsome man.

09:58.673 --> 10:00.265
He's a very grumpy man.

10:00.416 --> 10:02.083
He yelled at
me in Italian.

10:02.102 --> 10:04.436
And he doesn't even
look like Santa Claus.

10:04.512 --> 10:05.604
[sighs]

10:05.680 --> 10:06.663
What a cute store.

10:06.681 --> 10:08.422
I know, lovely.

10:08.442 --> 10:09.774
So nice.

10:09.851 --> 10:11.276
You know, Olivia asked
me to cancel all

10:11.427 --> 10:12.836
of the Christmas reservations

10:12.854 --> 10:13.945
but if you're really
serious

10:14.022 --> 10:15.505
You bet I'm serious.

10:15.523 --> 10:17.674
Olivia didn't wanna let
anyone down on Christmas

10:17.692 --> 10:19.509
and neither do I.

10:19.511 --> 10:21.511
Beebee, hello!

10:21.529 --> 10:22.787
Hi, Mrs. Myers.

10:22.864 --> 10:24.180
Beebee's one of my students.

10:24.199 --> 10:26.273
This is my good friend's
cousin, Natalie.

10:26.293 --> 10:27.517
How are you doing, Beebee?

10:27.535 --> 10:29.185
Uh, not's so good.

10:29.204 --> 10:31.521
I was hoping to get some temp
work in over vacation,

10:31.539 --> 10:32.797
but it seems
like everyone in town has

10:32.874 --> 10:34.115
already hired
the holiday help.

10:34.134 --> 10:35.467
Too bad.

10:35.618 --> 10:36.635
I'll keep an ear around.

10:36.786 --> 10:38.027
Thanks, Mrs. Myers.

10:38.046 --> 10:41.047
It was nice to meet
you, Ms. Natalie.

10:41.199 --> 10:43.366
Oh, there's
someone you should know,

10:43.385 --> 10:46.202
Miles Croaker, he's out
town culture vulture.

10:46.221 --> 10:47.795
[Natalie]
Culture vulture?

10:47.814 --> 10:50.707
You know, he oversees
all the town events,

10:50.725 --> 10:52.317
concerts and reviews
everything from

10:52.468 --> 10:54.152
the high school musical to
the local restaurants

10:54.303 --> 10:55.320
for the paper.

10:55.471 --> 10:57.471
Restaurant reviews, huh.

10:57.491 --> 11:00.158
He's tough, but fair
and very well-respected.

11:00.235 --> 11:02.994
He can make it work for
anyone in this town.

11:03.146 --> 11:04.329
[Miles]
Phew.

11:04.480 --> 11:06.890
Miles, dear,

11:06.908 --> 11:08.391
what's the matter?

11:08.410 --> 11:09.817
I haven't seen you this
distraught since the

11:09.836 --> 11:12.061
fizzing fireworks
fiasco of '09.

11:12.080 --> 11:15.064
Oh, it's this
Roman snow-blow.

11:15.083 --> 11:17.400
Oh, the blizzard
that hit Rome.

11:17.419 --> 11:19.402
Yeah, my cousin's stuck
there for Christmas.

11:19.421 --> 11:21.162
Oh, this storm's
has wreaked havoc on air

11:21.181 --> 11:22.681
travel all over the world.

11:22.757 --> 11:24.741
And in in Christmas.

11:24.743 --> 11:27.093
Oh, our touring carolers
just heard that flights home

11:27.245 --> 11:29.187
are canceled and
can't be rescheduled until

11:29.264 --> 11:31.022
after the holiday.

11:31.099 --> 11:33.191
It's terrible to be away
from home on Christmas.

11:33.342 --> 11:35.251
Hmm, yes, I was
hoping they'd be able to

11:35.270 --> 11:38.029
celebrate in the café,
it's closed on Christmas.

11:38.106 --> 11:39.756
Are most places closed then?

11:39.774 --> 11:41.199
Yes, all of them.

11:41.276 --> 11:43.109
Our poor carolers aren't
just stranded without

11:43.261 --> 11:45.094
their loved ones,

11:45.113 --> 11:47.872
but must also eat microwave
turkey dinners.

11:47.949 --> 11:49.207
Ew.

11:49.284 --> 11:50.767
[Miles]
Mm-mm.

11:50.769 --> 11:53.102
Can you please excuse me
I must call my travel agents

11:53.121 --> 11:55.797
again and see if there's
anything they can do.

11:57.125 --> 11:58.775
Those poor carolers.

11:58.793 --> 11:59.718
I don't suppose
you can do anything

11:59.869 --> 12:01.886
for their travel
agent front?

12:01.963 --> 12:03.555
I already tried
for my cousin Olivia,

12:03.631 --> 12:05.640
everything's locked up.

12:09.730 --> 12:10.895
[Natalie sighs]

12:11.047 --> 12:12.230
[Natalie]
It looks so beautiful.

12:12.381 --> 12:13.565
[Mrs. Myers chuckles]

12:13.641 --> 12:15.808
You know Olivia,
she always has to set up

12:15.961 --> 12:18.570
her decorations right after
Thanksgiving

12:18.646 --> 12:21.406
that way Christmas can last as
long as possible.

12:21.483 --> 12:23.658
[laughing]

12:24.745 --> 12:26.135
[sighs]

12:26.154 --> 12:28.896
You know she'd be here
if she could.

12:28.915 --> 12:30.473
Yeah.

12:30.492 --> 12:32.751
I know.

12:32.827 --> 12:34.419
I just can't remember the
last time I celebrated

12:34.570 --> 12:36.996
Christmas without her.

12:37.148 --> 12:38.882
[sighs]

12:40.335 --> 12:41.426
Oh, do you wanna stay
for dinner?

12:41.503 --> 12:43.094
Of course.

12:43.171 --> 12:45.655
I'm sure you can find something
in the freezer to cook.

12:45.673 --> 12:47.248
[chuckles]

12:47.267 --> 12:49.601
Cook?

12:49.752 --> 12:52.178
You did just wanna have a grand
restaurant opening, right?

12:52.330 --> 12:53.997
[laughs]

12:54.015 --> 12:56.691
Yeah, I just didn't think
I would be the one cooking.

13:00.763 --> 13:01.762
I better take this.

13:01.782 --> 13:04.357
Go ahead, make
yourself at home.

13:04.509 --> 13:06.009
Hey.

13:06.027 --> 13:08.011
I know.

13:08.029 --> 13:09.621
[sighs]

13:09.772 --> 13:11.623
Lasagne.

13:16.463 --> 13:18.797
Dishwasher,
this is the oven?

13:33.371 --> 13:35.555
I tried that one.

13:35.707 --> 13:37.464
Okay.

13:37.484 --> 13:39.984
Back to planning
Pezzo Di Parma.

13:57.745 --> 13:59.671
Who could that be?

14:04.419 --> 14:06.919
-Stefano.
-Ciao, Natalie.

14:07.072 --> 14:09.514
Uh, I made a sauce but uh,
now there is no one to eat it,

14:09.665 --> 14:11.850
so I thought maybe

14:12.001 --> 14:13.351
if you don't have any plans
for dinner,

14:13.502 --> 14:15.578
you can have.

14:15.597 --> 14:17.856
And some bone for
the cagnolino.

14:18.007 --> 14:20.674
Doggie bag for the doggie that's
very thoughtful, thank you.

14:20.694 --> 14:23.862
Prego.

14:23.938 --> 14:26.698
Oh, do you wanna come in
and join us for dinner?

14:26.849 --> 14:28.349
There's gotta be plenty.

14:28.368 --> 14:29.592
Are you sure?

14:29.611 --> 14:30.535
Yeah, I was just making
a lasa--

14:30.686 --> 14:32.111
[smoke alarm beeping]

14:32.263 --> 14:33.705
Oh no, the lasagne.

14:36.117 --> 14:37.375
Oh.

