Oh, you make pasta?

44:45.591 --> 44:48.267
I used to make pasta with
mia nonna every Natale.

44:49.354 --> 44:51.187
It uh, it was my
favorite part.

44:52.432 --> 44:55.266
But uh, I can help.

44:55.418 --> 44:57.176
Oh, you cook?

44:57.195 --> 44:59.987
Of course,
I love to cook.

45:01.366 --> 45:03.533
But you're our guest,
we couldn't possibly make you

45:04.777 --> 45:06.703
work in the kitchen.

45:06.779 --> 45:09.430
Make me, no, I want to.

45:09.449 --> 45:10.431
We'd love your help.

45:10.433 --> 45:11.432
Let me get you an apron.

45:11.434 --> 45:12.375
Andiamo.

45:12.526 --> 45:13.434
[Ariella]
Okay.

45:13.436 --> 45:15.937
Great.

45:15.955 --> 45:18.197
[blows raspberry]

45:18.216 --> 45:21.050
[speaking Italian]

45:58.664 --> 45:59.922
Hmm.

46:00.074 --> 46:01.424
[speaking Italian]

46:11.102 --> 46:13.019
[sighs]

46:23.097 --> 46:25.172
They're waiting for us.

46:25.174 --> 46:26.449
Okay, I'm ready.

46:28.511 --> 46:30.620
Um, Chef Stefano.

46:32.698 --> 46:35.625
How'd you come with your
logical list of

46:35.701 --> 46:37.852
qualities you're looking
for in a woman?

46:37.870 --> 46:40.521
Well, I thought about it
and she didn't make sense to me.

46:40.523 --> 46:42.356
Why what's the matter?

46:42.358 --> 46:44.859
Oh, nothing, nothing.

46:44.877 --> 46:46.219
I just I guess I just
haven't done enough thinking.

46:47.196 --> 46:49.380
Andiamo.

46:49.532 --> 46:52.308
Baked brie with olive tabouli,
minestrone reteta,

46:52.459 --> 46:54.702
ricotta and spinach
tortellini,

46:54.720 --> 46:57.038
braised beef in Merlot
wine sauce and something

46:57.056 --> 46:59.106
called, "Panettone".

47:00.985 --> 47:03.060
Sounds wonderful.

47:03.212 --> 47:06.138
But I'm afraid Stefano's
multo-italiano menu

47:06.157 --> 47:08.658
isn't gonna trigger any warm
American fuzzies.

47:09.977 --> 47:12.053
I make these
really good cookie bars.

47:12.071 --> 47:14.313
Well, it's a start.

47:14.332 --> 47:16.666
I know, we can make
a big batch of cookies

47:16.742 --> 47:18.150
and then take
the tray into the town

47:18.169 --> 47:20.061
Christmas Cookie
Swap this afternoon.

47:20.063 --> 47:22.338
Christmas Cookie Swap?

47:22.415 --> 47:23.840
This afternoon?

47:23.916 --> 47:26.734
Beebee, you just
baked my day.

47:26.752 --> 47:28.845
[laughing]

47:28.996 --> 47:30.179
Ooh, but we're gonna have
to hurry

47:30.256 --> 47:31.238
if we'll be ready
on time.

47:31.240 --> 47:32.139
Come on.

47:45.104 --> 47:47.446
Just like shake some in.

47:53.613 --> 47:54.595
Oh!

47:54.614 --> 47:56.497
[Beebee groaning]

48:04.290 --> 48:05.530
Okay.

48:05.550 --> 48:07.124
All over.

48:07.276 --> 48:08.968
Everywhere.

48:12.557 --> 48:13.389
Oh, looks pretty great.

48:13.540 --> 48:14.615
Perfect.

48:14.634 --> 48:16.467
Good job.

48:16.619 --> 48:17.852
[Natalie]
Alright, to the fridge.

48:22.400 --> 48:24.291
Now we just 30 minutes
while it sets.

48:24.310 --> 48:26.569
You better set a timer,
can't rely on a smoke alarm

48:26.720 --> 48:29.906
for this one.

48:37.807 --> 48:40.658
So I ordered all the place cards
and the menu cards,

48:40.810 --> 48:42.919
I know you wanted to write
them up by hand

48:43.070 --> 48:45.755
but until Chef Stefano
finalizes the menu

48:48.927 --> 48:49.926
Ms. Natalie.

48:50.077 --> 48:52.595
It's like
Olio d'oliva descadoni

48:52.672 --> 48:54.513
is some kind of--

48:56.008 --> 48:57.158
Ms. Natalie!

48:57.176 --> 48:58.492
Culinary food myth,

48:58.511 --> 49:01.162
like free-range foie gras

49:01.164 --> 49:02.104
or guilt-free ice cream.

49:02.181 --> 49:03.330
Ms. Natalie!

49:03.349 --> 49:04.999
Oh, I'm sorry, what?

49:05.017 --> 49:06.025
It's time.

49:09.930 --> 49:12.073
Hurry, we're gonna
be late for the swap.

49:19.606 --> 49:21.015
Okay, go, go, go!

49:21.017 --> 49:22.208
[Natalie]
Hats, coats, gloves,
it's cold!

49:27.373 --> 49:29.614
The secret to a clean
kitchen is simple,

49:29.634 --> 49:30.967
don't cook ever.

49:40.386 --> 49:41.885
Porca vacca!

49:42.038 --> 49:43.037
[Tyler]
What, what, oh sorry,
what happened?

49:43.039 --> 49:43.980
What?

49:44.056 --> 49:46.874
I can't see.

49:46.892 --> 49:48.133
[Tyler]
Holy cow!

49:48.152 --> 49:51.045
That's what I said,
eh, not exactly,

49:51.047 --> 49:52.546
but you get the idea.

49:52.548 --> 49:54.323
What happened?

49:54.400 --> 49:55.825
There's only one
thing I can think of that

49:55.976 --> 49:57.885
can cause so much damage
to a kitchen

49:57.887 --> 49:58.977
in so short of a time.

49:58.997 --> 50:00.888
Rabid badgers?

50:00.906 --> 50:02.999
Rabid badgers, Natalie!

50:03.150 --> 50:05.501
Oh yeah.

50:05.652 --> 50:07.652
Yeah, that make
that makes sense.

50:07.672 --> 50:08.896
Well, look look at least
the smoke alarm isn't

50:08.898 --> 50:10.914
going off yet.

50:11.067 --> 50:12.733
This feast of Natale is not
gonna work.

50:12.752 --> 50:13.901
Why do you say that?

50:13.919 --> 50:16.495
Because we used
up our Christmas miracle

50:16.514 --> 50:19.181
when Natalie didn't burn
the whole place down.

50:20.334 --> 50:21.183
[sighs]

50:24.096 --> 50:26.247
Okay, are we late,
did we make it on time?

50:26.265 --> 50:28.190
Uh no, we made it.

50:28.342 --> 50:29.525
Wooh.

50:29.676 --> 50:32.361
[indistinct chatter
and laughter]

50:36.275 --> 50:37.591
There's free samples.

50:37.593 --> 50:38.759
Don't say it.

50:38.778 --> 50:41.520
That's because you're one
smart cookie.

50:41.539 --> 50:42.538
[grunts]

50:48.454 --> 50:50.695
[Natalie]
Big beautiful bars, thank you.

50:50.715 --> 50:52.773
Thank you.

50:52.792 --> 50:54.775
Ooh, maybe we
should do two, alright?

50:54.794 --> 50:55.885
Thank you.

50:55.961 --> 50:57.461
Hmm, yummy.

50:57.538 --> 50:59.280
They almost look like a little
reindeer poop or something.

50:59.282 --> 51:00.556
[laughs]

51:00.633 --> 51:01.782
-It it has to be.
-They're really good.

51:01.784 --> 51:03.617
Yeah.

51:03.636 --> 51:04.785
Gingerbread cookie.

51:04.804 --> 51:05.710
Thank you.

51:05.730 --> 51:07.521
Merry Christmas.

51:13.145 --> 51:15.053
Beebee, did we forget
to turn the oven off

51:15.073 --> 51:16.463
or something?

51:16.465 --> 51:19.316
We never turned it on.

51:19.468 --> 51:21.560
Oh, but maybe we
forgot to tidy up.

51:21.579 --> 51:23.061
I didn't forget,
we really didn't have time.

51:23.081 --> 51:24.305
Natalie, what is that?
What is this?

51:24.323 --> 51:25.973
This cooking, huh?

51:25.975 --> 51:26.974
What is this?

51:26.992 --> 51:29.251
Hmm?

51:29.403 --> 51:32.088
I'm sorry,
I think we may have left

51:32.239 --> 51:34.924
the kitchen a little
not clean.

51:36.335 --> 51:37.593
Not clean.

51:37.670 --> 51:40.654
I come inside and I take
a look and I say

51:40.673 --> 51:42.914
what'd I say-- What I--

51:42.934 --> 51:44.992
[speaks Italian]

51:44.994 --> 51:47.853
[speaks Italian]

51:50.850 --> 51:53.834
Oh, grande like grand,
a big a big mess.

51:53.853 --> 51:55.836
Uh yeah,
it's a big mess.

51:55.855 --> 51:57.855
We have only one day left,
so much to do

51:58.007 --> 52:00.116
and you run off
for this.

52:00.192 --> 52:02.952
Uh, why don't you take
my half

52:03.028 --> 52:05.696
and head back to the restaurant
and get started on the clean-up.

52:05.848 --> 52:06.847
Hmm.

52:06.849 --> 52:07.514
Explain to me.

52:07.516 --> 52:09.107
Yeah, I'll help.

52:09.127 --> 52:11.109
Oh, you don't have to do that,
it wasn't your mess.

52:11.129 --> 52:13.354
No, no,
I wanna help.

52:13.372 --> 52:15.131
You do?

52:15.207 --> 52:17.466
Yeah, Chef Stefano scares me
when he's like this.

52:17.618 --> 52:19.451
I don't even know what these
cookies are?

52:19.470 --> 52:22.471
Oh look, these are shortbreads

52:22.548 --> 52:25.457
with a little um,
icing drizzl,

52:25.476 --> 52:28.310
and this little gingerbread man.

52:29.630 --> 52:31.705
Little gingerbread man,

52:31.724 --> 52:33.056
"Can't catch me,
I'm a gingerbread man."

52:33.209 --> 52:34.224
No, no,
no, no, no, no.

52:34.377 --> 52:36.226
No, no, Natalie.

52:36.379 --> 52:38.988
This is an Italian feast
of Natale,

52:39.064 --> 52:41.899
not the American
feast of cookie.

52:42.051 --> 52:43.717
-Capito?
-Mhmm.

52:43.736 --> 52:45.494
We will do panettone

52:45.646 --> 52:48.330
made by my family recipe,
capisce?

52:50.001 --> 52:51.667
-And the cookies.
-Mamma mia.

52:51.818 --> 52:53.836
[Natalie]
I read on Miles' reviews,
I think he would really like

52:53.913 --> 52:55.078
[Miles]
Uh, Natalie.

52:55.231 --> 52:56.230
Stefano.

52:56.248 --> 52:58.340
Speak of the devil.

52:58.492 --> 52:59.583
Hello.

52:59.735 --> 53:01.326
-Ariella, ciao.
-Ciao, Stefano.

53:01.345 --> 53:02.403
[kissing]

53:02.421 --> 53:03.420
Mr. Croaker.

53:03.572 --> 53:04.496
-Natalie, ciao.
-Hello.

53:04.515 --> 53:07.165
[kissing]

53:07.185 --> 53:10.001
Well, everybody is so excited
and looking forward

53:10.021 --> 53:11.595
to your feast of Natale.

53:11.747 --> 53:12.913
[laughs]

53:12.932 --> 53:14.190
So are we.

53:14.266 --> 53:15.524
We uh, we're just gonna
head back there and get

53:15.676 --> 53:16.859
some things ready.

53:17.010 --> 53:19.195
We want it all to
be just perfect.

53:19.271 --> 53:21.088
That means you're coming to
the Christmas festival,

53:21.106 --> 53:22.423
it's about to start.

53:22.441 --> 53:24.258
Oh, no, no,
there is so much to do.

53:24.276 --> 53:25.517
-Sorry, yeah.
-[Natalie] So much to do.

53:25.536 --> 53:27.018
More than ever.

53:27.038 --> 53:29.020
But it's our first
annual Christmas festival,

53:29.040 --> 53:30.355
you must come.

53:30.374 --> 53:32.766
We need everyone to
make it a success.

53:32.768 --> 53:35.769
I organized it myself.

53:35.771 --> 53:37.028
If you insist.

53:37.048 --> 53:39.531
We'll be there with bells on.

53:39.550 --> 53:41.383
-Like jingle bells.
-[Stefano] Oh.

53:41.460 --> 53:43.886
Um, cool uh,

53:44.037 --> 53:45.554
we'll just go get ready now.

53:45.706 --> 53:46.722
-See you soon.
-Do that.

53:46.873 --> 53:48.891
See you soon.

53:55.307 --> 53:58.150
[indistinct chatter]

54:06.911 --> 54:09.486
Alright, alright,
this way.

54:09.638 --> 54:10.579
Get on there.

54:14.326 --> 54:15.309
Okay, you there.

54:15.327 --> 54:17.311
[laughing]

54:17.329 --> 54:18.236
Okay, ready.

54:18.256 --> 54:19.421
Cheese.

54:24.095 --> 54:25.652
-[Tyler] Yes!
-[Stall holder] Congratulations!

54:25.671 --> 54:28.079
Thank you.

54:28.099 --> 54:29.990
Here.

54:30.009 --> 54:31.433
Thank you.

54:36.015 --> 54:37.273
[Miles]
Oh, you're here!

54:37.424 --> 54:38.499
[laughs]

54:38.501 --> 54:39.833
I have just the thing.

54:39.852 --> 54:41.610
Right this way.

54:41.687 --> 54:44.446
Oh uh, but first, picture.

54:46.600 --> 54:48.342
Right, right, here we go!

54:48.344 --> 54:49.860
Here we go, have to
keep the line moving.

54:50.012 --> 54:52.538
[laughs]

54:56.627 --> 54:58.109
Sit down, Sparky.

54:58.129 --> 54:59.753
Sit down.

55:06.712 --> 55:08.045
This one looks fun.

55:08.197 --> 55:09.972
Oh yeah, sure.

55:12.292 --> 55:14.125
Thanks.

55:14.145 --> 55:15.218
Go first.

55:15.371 --> 55:17.871
Sure, yeah.

55:17.890 --> 55:20.374
Okay, wooh.

55:20.392 --> 55:21.466
Aw.

55:21.485 --> 55:23.402
No good, here
let me try.

55:29.068 --> 55:30.617
It's okay.

55:36.000 --> 55:37.649
Do you feel okay?

55:37.668 --> 55:40.169
Yeah.

55:40.245 --> 55:42.654
How do I look
like I'm feeling?

55:42.673 --> 55:45.341
Well, I don't know,
but but nothing good.

55:52.925 --> 55:55.768
[taking deep breaths]

55:58.764 --> 56:01.690
So uh, have you seen

56:01.767 --> 56:04.526
any good Kung fu
movies lately?

56:05.863 --> 56:07.863
Mm, nope.

56:08.014 --> 56:09.923
Why?

56:09.925 --> 56:11.700
Uh, just just curious.

56:15.948 --> 56:18.265
What about baseball games?

56:18.283 --> 56:19.783
In December?

56:19.935 --> 56:21.118
Well, at least you know they
don't play baseball

56:21.270 --> 56:22.211
in the winter.

56:22.362 --> 56:24.880
Yeah, well,
that's all I know, so

56:29.962 --> 56:32.221
Yeah, I forgot to
ask uh, about what you do

56:32.297 --> 56:33.463
in the city?

56:33.616 --> 56:34.723
What is your job?

56:34.800 --> 56:37.017
Oh, I'm a Jacklyn
of all trades.

56:39.138 --> 56:41.897
I watch the dogs

56:41.974 --> 56:43.232
and design custom prints,

56:43.383 --> 56:46.568
do specialty gift-wrapping,
plan events and parties,

56:46.720 --> 56:49.071
and about a hundred other
things.

56:49.222 --> 56:50.406
Huh, why do you
do so many things?

56:50.557 --> 56:52.825
Why don't you
just do one thing?

56:54.227 --> 56:56.227
I don't know,
I guess I just never found

56:56.247 --> 56:59.081
the right thing and so
I kept trying new things.

56:59.232 --> 57:01.975
Hmm, when I was 3 years old

57:01.994 --> 57:04.670
my Zio Lorenzo,
he put a knife in my hand

57:05.998 --> 57:08.072
and I knew I would be a chef.

57:08.092 --> 57:10.259
That is all I ever
wanna be.

57:10.335 --> 57:13.170
Your Zio Lorenzo
gave a butcher's knife to

57:13.322 --> 57:14.504
a 3-year-old?

57:14.657 --> 57:16.748
No.

57:16.767 --> 57:19.268
Maybe I exaggerate
a little bit, huh?

57:19.419 --> 57:21.395
Well, maybe
you're exaggerating now.

57:23.757 --> 57:26.275
Maybe you're afraid, huh?

57:27.519 --> 57:29.736
I'm not scared of anything.

57:32.858 --> 57:34.533
Except perhaps the cold, yes?

57:37.196 --> 57:38.770
It's not that bad.

57:38.789 --> 57:40.622
No, you're cold.

58:13.899 --> 58:15.232
What's that?

58:15.384 --> 58:16.399
What's what?

58:16.552 --> 58:18.660
The piece of paper
you keep checking.

58:18.812 --> 58:21.722
What, what piece of paper?

58:21.740 --> 58:24.166
The one in your pocket.

58:24.243 --> 58:26.818
Um

58:26.837 --> 58:27.744
Catch!

58:27.896 --> 58:28.912
No!

58:29.064 --> 58:29.821
Beebee, Beebee,
no, no, no, no.

58:29.840 --> 58:31.398
Don't, don't.

58:31.400 --> 58:32.841
Oh, what is it,
a letter to Santa?

58:32.993 --> 58:34.401
[Tyler]
Don't just don't just don't
just don't just

58:34.419 --> 58:36.570
can can you give it back
to me please, Beebee?

58:36.572 --> 58:39.348
[indistinct chatter in
background]

58:50.753 --> 58:53.695
What is this?

58:53.772 --> 58:56.490
"My smile, awesomeness,
likes baseball."

59:00.371 --> 59:02.020
What is this, like a list
of things I'm supposed to be

59:02.039 --> 59:03.539
or something?

59:03.690 --> 59:06.433
No, it's--

59:06.435 --> 59:08.285
I'm not hardly
any of these things.

59:08.437 --> 59:10.045
Beebee, it's not
like that, it's just--

59:13.959 --> 59:14.958
I was just
trying to be logical,

59:15.110 --> 59:17.886
that's all.

59:18.038 --> 59:19.946
You're a jerk.

59:19.965 --> 59:21.848
Beebee.

59:23.227 --> 59:24.560
Beebee.

59:37.816 --> 59:39.241
Beebee,
what's the matter?

59:39.392 --> 59:40.242
What happened?

59:40.393 --> 59:41.410
Are you okay?

59:41.486 --> 59:43.637
It's Tyler, he's being
really logical.

59:43.655 --> 59:45.080
I can't

59:45.231 --> 59:47.916
Okay, let's go have some cocoa,
you can tell me about it.

59:49.402 --> 59:51.253
Grazie.

1:00:01.840 --> 1:00:04.825
Why don't you
start at the beginning?

1:00:04.827 --> 1:00:07.844
We were at the Santa
sling booth and I was

1:00:07.996 --> 1:00:09.730
I was trying to figure out
how Tyler felt about me.

1:00:11.442 --> 1:00:13.850
He started asking all
these stupid questions

1:00:14.002 --> 1:00:16.519
about Kung fu, baseball,
checking

1:00:16.672 --> 1:00:17.762
his stupid list.

1:00:17.781 --> 1:00:20.115
[sighs]

1:00:21.693 --> 1:00:24.027
[Beebee]
He said he was just trying
to be logical.

1:00:24.179 --> 1:00:26.771
But then he can't possibly
like me,

1:00:26.790 --> 1:00:28.957
I don't like any of the things
on the stupid list,

1:00:30.869 --> 1:00:33.795
especially

1:00:33.947 --> 1:00:35.372
not the nice
smile part.

1:00:35.524 --> 1:00:37.132
Oh.

1:00:37.209 --> 1:00:40.135
Beebee, hey.

1:00:40.286 --> 1:00:42.529
Your smile is lovely

1:00:42.547 --> 1:00:45.289
just how it is, I promise.

1:00:45.309 --> 1:00:47.768
What could give Tyler such
a silly idea like this?

1:00:50.205 --> 1:00:52.648
"Speaks Italian,

1:00:52.799 --> 1:00:54.983
lives at the same place,
loves to cook."

1:00:58.656 --> 1:01:00.380
You okay?

1:01:00.382 --> 1:01:01.715
Yeah.

1:01:01.717 --> 1:01:04.451
Of course, um,
what happened next?

1:01:06.405 --> 1:01:08.388
Well, I decided my intuition
was telling me

1:01:08.407 --> 1:01:10.666
Tyler is a jerk
and I left.

1:01:14.838 --> 1:01:17.673
But maybe you should
just sleep on it, yeah?

1:01:19.176 --> 1:01:21.084
Give your intuition some
time to think it over.

1:01:21.236 --> 1:01:23.253
Yeah, I think I'll do that.

1:01:23.405 --> 1:01:25.347
Christmas is exhausting.

1:01:28.852 --> 1:01:31.687
[sighs]

1:01:33.916 --> 1:01:35.857
Everything okay?

1:01:36.009 --> 1:01:38.768
You know, I think I'm just gonna
go back to the restaurant.

1:01:38.921 --> 1:01:41.029
But the festival
is important.

1:01:43.108 --> 1:01:44.774
[speaking Italian]

1:01:44.927 --> 1:01:46.609
Si.

1:01:46.762 --> 1:01:49.520
And Natalie is here,
too.

1:01:49.540 --> 1:01:51.614
But we were thinking uh,
we're gonna go back,

1:01:51.767 --> 1:01:52.782
it's there's so much to do.

1:01:52.935 --> 1:01:54.209
Oh no, you don't have to go,
too.

1:01:54.286 --> 1:01:57.270
You can stay,
I'm sure you want to.

1:01:57.272 --> 1:01:58.621
What, and let
you do all the work?

